 book will appeal to students and scholars of world Christianity, missiology, and the history of Christianity, as well as Southeast Asian studies, secular sociologies, and anthropologists operating within the field of religious studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCambodianszFrancexReligion. 0aCambodianszUnited StatesxReligion. 0aChristian convertszCambodia. 0aChristianityzCambodia. 0aEvangelicalismzCambodia. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh  aCambodia.  aCambodian Civil War.  aKhmer.  aTheravada Buddhism.  aWorld Christianity.  aconversion.  aethnographic study of indigenous Cambodian evangelicalism.  aethnography.  aevangelicalism.  agenocide.  amultiple religious belonging.  areserve mission.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271096667?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271096667423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271096667/original  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles